<h2 id=3D"HotelSourcingApplication(MockProjectfor.NETCorepractice)-Assumpti=
ons">Assumptions</h2>
<p></p>
<ul>
<li><p>Merchant will only see the hotel listing data being displayed inside=
 Shopify Admin console.</p></li>
<li><p>There are no graphical user interface needed to trigger the import o=
f hotel data.</p></li>
<li><p>The execution of exporting and importing process will be represented=
 as a set of <strong>.NET 5 web services</strong> (.NET Core Web API)</p></=
li>
<li><p>HotelBeds REST API documentation is provided here (<a href=3D"https:=
//developer.hotelbeds.com/" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" class=3D"extern=
al-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://developer.hotelbeds.com/</a> )</p></li>
<li><p>HotelBeds provides 3 suites of API (Hotels, Activities, Transfers). =
In the scope of this project, the developer will use <strong>Hotels APIs su=
ite</strong>.</p></li>
<li><p>In order to send request, developer needs to get api key, secret, an=
d X-Signature from my hotelBeds account. X-Signature value will be calculat=
ed from api key and secret, using <strong>the provided script</strong>.</p>=
</li>
<li><p>The API key provided will only give me access to hotelBeds' test env=
ironment, with a limited allowed quota of <strong>50 requests per day</stro=
ng>.</p></li>
<li><p>Inside Hotels API suite, there are 3 types: <strong>BookingAPI</stro=
ng> (covering the complete booking process), <strong>ContentAPI</strong> (r=
eturning static information needed for BookingAPI), <strong>CacheAPI </stro=
ng>(saving data in zip files and return them upon request). The data saved =
in Shopify should be <em>a combination</em> of these 3 response results. Ho=
wever, for the scope of this project, developer can use only ContentAPI and=
 BookingAPI.</p></li>
<li><p>ContentAPI <strong>cannot</strong> be used to retrieve <strong>stati=
c</strong> information in real-time. This could result in the blocking of c=
redentials. HotelBeds recommends that users should set up a <strong>batch p=
rocess</strong> to retrieve the info from them on a periodic basis, and a <=
strong>database</strong> on their side to store the retrieved information a=
nd be able to use it when needed.</p></li>
<li><p>Shopify provides access to REST Admin API and GraphQL Admin API, whi=
ch can be used to access the store inventory information. For the scope of =
this project, we will use <strong>GraphQL Admin API</strong> because it sup=
port bulk product operations. Documentation is provided here (<a href=3D"ht=
tps://shopify.dev/api/admin" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" class=3D"exter=
nal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://shopify.dev/api/admin</a> )</p></li>
<li><p>Shopify Admin API enforces <strong>rate limits</strong> on all reque=
st, so responsible API calls in the code should be taken into consideration=
. (<a href=3D"https://shopify.dev/api/usage/rate-limits" data-card-appearan=
ce=3D"inline" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://shopify.dev/=
api/usage/rate-limits</a> )</p></li>
<li><p>For now, OC should only contain hotel listings from the following de=
stinations in USA:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>San Diego, Los Angeles, San Francisco, Joshua Trees, Big Sur, Malibu=
, Santa Barbara</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li><p>For now, OC should only contain hotel listings from the following de=
stinations in Mexico:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Cancun, Holbox, Tulum, Puerto Vallanta, Sayulita, Nayrit, Baja Ca, P=
uerto To Escodido, Oxcaca, San Migule, Mexico City, Rivera Maya</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
